defaultCards.name: Carleton Moore
defaultCards.facts: Cam got his BS in EECS from the University of Colorado. He helps run the Collaborative Software Development Laboratory.

defaultCards.name: Philip Johnson
defaultCards.facts: Philip got his BS in CS from the University of Michigan (along with a BS in Biology!). He co-founded the Geo Garden Club, an app that connects local gardeners.

defaultCards.name: Kim Binsted
defaultCards.facts: Kim is a Professor of Information and Computer Sciences at the University of Hawaii, Director of the Collaborative Software Development Laboratory, and the CEO of OpenPowerQuality.com.

defaultCards.name: Scott Robertson
defaultCards.facts: Research Areas include: Sociotechnical systems, Human-computer interaction, Social media and civic engagement,Digital government (e-Participation), AI, and computer-science education

defaultCards.name: Nodari Sitchinava
defaultCards.facts: Research focuses on algorithms for modern parallel systems. Most recently, have been working on cache-efficient parallel algorithms for multicores and GPUs

defaultCards.name: Daniel Suthers
defaultCards.facts: General Areas of expertise include: Cognitive, social and computational perspectives on designing and evaluating software for learning, collaboration, and community. Analytic methods for studying use of such technology.

defaultCards.name: Depeng Li
defaultCards.facts: Dr. Depeng Li has been working as Associate Professor in department of Information and Computer Sciences (ICS) at University of Hawaii at Manoa (UHM) since 2018.

defaultCards.name: Henri Casanova
defaultCards.facts: Casanova's area of research fits broadly under the High Performance Computing umbrella, and teaches a range of undergraduate and graduate courses.

defaultCards.name: Edo Biagioni
defaultCards.facts: Biagioni is interested in networking, particularly decentralized and ad-hoc networking, often with security aspects. He is also interested in wireless networking, and in the issues of power, security, routing, and reliability in wireless networks, particularly wireless sensor networks.

defaultCards.name: Daniel Port
defaultCards.facts: Research Interests include : Actionable Business Analytics, Information Technology Engineering, Strategic, Economic, and Empirical Methods in Software Engineering, and IT Education

defaultCards.name: Elijah Myles Saloma
defaultCards.facts: He achieved 1st place in ballroom dancing nationally! He also assists students with Calculus 2 work.
